"title": "5946: sensitivity",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5946: sensitivity",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Deep feelings for others and sympathy for their needs, leading to appropriate action on their behalf. Spiritual sensitivity is the ability to perceive and respond to the call of God or the spiritual demands of the moment. Oversensitivity and lack of sensitivity are extremes to be avoided.</p>\n<h2>God's sensitivity to his people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:7\">EXO 3:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:18\">JDG 2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:2\">ISA 40:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:22\">LAM 3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:14\">HOS 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:78\">LUK 1:78</a></p>\n<h2>Sensitivity shown by Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:20\">MAT 12:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:3\">ISA 42:3</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:37\">MAT 23:37</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:34\">LUK 13:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:12-Luke7:13\">LUK 7:12–7:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:41\">LUK 19:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:34-John9:35\">JHN 9:34–9:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:33-John11:35\">JHN 11:33–11:35</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's own experience of temptation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:14-Heb4:15\">HEB 4:14–4:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:18\">HEB 2:18</a></p>\n<h2>Sensitivity to others</h2>\n<h3>Arises from an experience of God's compassion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:3-2Cor1:4\">2CO 1:3–1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:1\">PHP 2:1</a></p>\n<h3>Believers urged to show sensitivity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:15\">ROM 12:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:2\">ISA 40:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:32\">EPH 4:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12-Col3:13\">COL 3:12–3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:8\">1PE 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:3\">HEB 13:3</a></p>\n<h3>Sensitivity to foreigners in Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:9\">EXO 23:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:21\">EXO 22:21</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:33-Lev19:34\">LEV 19:33–19:34</a></p>\n<h3>Sensitivity to those in distress</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:11-Job2:13\">JOB 2:11–2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:38-Matt26:40\">MAT 26:38–26:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:34-Mark14:37\">MRK 14:34–14:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:5-2Cor7:7\">2CO 7:5–7:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:33-Heb10:34\">HEB 10:33–10:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:27\">JAS 1:27</a></p>\n<h3>Sensitivity to those weak in faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:1\">ROM 15:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:1-Rom14:3\">ROM 14:1–14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:15\">ROM 14:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:9-1Cor8:12\">1CO 8:9–8:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:7\">1TH 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>Sensitivity in speech</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:23\">PRO 15:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:24\">PRO 16:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:11\">PRO 25:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:15\">PRO 25:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:15\">1PE 3:15</a></p>\n<h2>Insensitivity to others</h2>\n<h3>Examples of insensitivity to others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:53-Deut28:57\">DEU 28:53–28:57</a> <em>As a result of God's judgment, the most sensitive person will become insensitive even to the needs of family</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:13-1Sam1:14\">1SA 1:13–1:14</a> <em>Eli's insensitivity to Hannah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job16:2\">JOB 16:2</a> <em>the insensitivity of Job's “comforters”</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah4:9-Jonah4:11\">JON 4:9–4:11</a> <em>Jonah's insensitivity to the people of Nineveh</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:13\">MAT 19:13</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:13\">MRK 10:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:15\">LUK 18:15</a> <em>the disciples' insensitivity towards children brought to Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:20-1Cor11:21\">1CO 11:20–11:21</a> <em>insensitivity to the needs of others</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:2-Jas2:4\">JAS 2:2–2:4</a> <em>insensitivity towards poorer visitors to church</em></p>\n<h3>The results of insensitivity</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:20\">PSA 69:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:17\">PRO 25:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:20\">PRO 25:20</a></p>\n<h2>Oversensitivity</h2>\n<h3>Oversensitivity in the face of rejection</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:11-1Sam25:13\">1SA 25:11–25:13</a> <em>David's hasty reaction towards Nabal</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:53-Luke9:54\">LUK 9:53–9:54</a> <em>James' and John's hasty reaction</em></p>\n<h3>Oversensitivity of conscience</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:2\">ROM 14:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:6-1Cor8:8\">1CO 8:6–8:8</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual sensitivity</h2>\n<h3>Spiritual awareness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam3:8\">1SA 3:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:32-Matt24:34\">MAT 24:32–24:34</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:28-Mark13:29\">MRK 13:28–13:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:29-Luke21:30\">LUK 21:29–21:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:9-Acts16:10\">ACT 16:9–16:10</a></p>\n<h3>Lack of spiritual sensitivity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:18-Eph4:19\">EPH 4:18–4:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:31-Prov23:35\">PRO 23:31–23:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:28-Rom1:29\">ROM 1:28–1:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:1-1Tim4:4\">1TI 4:1–4:4</a>ISA <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim42:25\">42:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:3\">JER 5:3</a>EZK <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:2\">12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech7:11-Zech7:14\">ZEC 7:11–7:14</a></p>\n<h3>God hardens human hearts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:3\">EXO 7:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:24-Rom1:25\">ROM 1:24–1:25</a></p>",
